<span id="freeTextContainer6841525299549661967">I really really liked this book. I would give it 4 1/2 stars if that was an option. It started a little slowly, but once I got into it I really enjoyed it. It has a great message, a likable (if sometimes exasperating) main character, and a cute little love story. I thought that it was kind of weird how abruptly the love story suddenly resolved itself, but I like happy endings so I guess I am okay with it. I really enjoyed the writing style. It was very clever and funny, and full of sentences lik</span>
  <span id="freeText6841525299549661967" style="display:none">I really really liked this book. I would give it 4 1/2 stars if that was an option. It started a little slowly, but once I got into it I really enjoyed it. It has a great message, a likable (if sometimes exasperating) main character, and a cute little love story. I thought that it was kind of weird how abruptly the love story suddenly resolved itself, but I like happy endings so I guess I am okay with it. I really enjoyed the writing style. It was very clever and funny, and full of sentences like, "He would today atone for all his failures to be what she wanted him to be by going cheerfully into an affair which, he suspected, would establish his utter asshood as a fact beyond controversy in the opinion of any sensible person present." Love it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6841525299549661967" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

